name: Latex Diffusion V2 LORA
description:
Finally got the time and ways to make a LORA based on the same dataset as my Latex Diffusion Model+Merge.
This was very much needed because of the trend of LORAs and also how practical they are: You can use them with any model and tweak the strenght yoursel.

Only did a bit of testing but so far it seems
- below 0.5 creates mostly basic suits
- the lower the strenght, the more diverse they get and or you turn normal clothes into latex
- higher strenght results in latex corsets even if not prompted
- latex masks are difficult to get (requires more testing, maybe even as second additional LORA)

Overall tip: use tags like "latex mask, latex corset, exposed breasts, nude, naked" if you do or do not want certain things to generate.
